## 7. Feature Specifications

### 7.1 Authentication & Role System

**Roles and Permissions:**

| Permission | Admin | Manager | Staff |
|---|---|---|---|
| Manage users | | | |
| Configure categories/fields | | | |
| Add/edit/delete products | | | |
| Record stock movements | | | |
| View inventory & dashboard | | | |
| Export reports | | | |
| View movement history | | | |
| Process sales (optional) | | | |

**Implementation:**
- Passwords hashed with `bcrypt` (salt rounds: 12)
- JWT tokens with 8-hour expiry, stored in `httpOnly` cookie (not localStorage)
- Refresh token mechanism for seamless sessions
- Failed login lockout after 5 attempts (15-minute cooldown)

---

### 7.2 Product Category & Field Builder (The Core Engine)

This is the most critical module. It allows the admin to define what a "product" looks like for their business.

**Admin can:**
1. Create a category (e.g., "Medicines", "Electronics", "Clothing")
2. Add custom fields to each category:
   - Field label: "Batch Number"
   - Field key: auto-generated as `batch_number`
   - Type: Text / Number / Date / Dropdown / Boolean / Textarea
   - Required: Yes/No
   - Options (for dropdowns): comma-separated values
   - Unit: optional suffix ("kg", "ml", "pcs")
3. Reorder fields via drag-and-drop
4. Edit or delete fields (with warning if products exist)
5. Assign a color and icon to the category for visual identification

**Frontend behavior:**
- When adding/editing a product, the form dynamically renders only the fields for that product's category
- Required fields are validated before submission
- Dropdown fields render as `<select>` elements with the defined options
- Date fields render as date pickers

---

### 7.3 Product Management

**Features:**
- Add, edit, deactivate products (soft delete  never hard delete)
- SKU auto-generation (or manual entry) with uniqueness check
- Barcode value field (can match SKU or be separate)
- Product image upload (stored locally in `/uploads/`, served as static files)
- Search by name, SKU, barcode
- Filter by category, stock status (in stock / low stock / out of stock)
- Sort by name, quantity, price, last updated
- Bulk import via CSV upload (template downloadable)

---

### 7.4 Inventory Management (Real-Time)

**Core functionality:**
- Each product has stock tracked per **location** (e.g., "Main Warehouse", "Store Front")
- Real-time quantity displayed  updates live via Socket.IO when any user makes a change
- Low stock badge shown when `quantity <= minStock`

**Stock operations:**
- **Stock In:** receive goods (with optional reference/invoice number)
- **Stock Out:** remove stock (with reason/note)
- **Adjustment:** correct stock count (with mandatory reason)
- **Transfer:** move stock between locations

**Each operation:**
- Requires a note/reason
- Logged immediately to `StockMovement` table
- Broadcasts `stock:updated` event via Socket.IO to all connected clients
- Cannot be deleted (audit trail  only adjustments are allowed)

---

### 7.5 Dashboard (Real-Time)

**Widgets:**
- Total products count
- Total stock value (sum of `quantity × price` across all products)
- Low stock items (count + list)
- Out-of-stock items (count)
- Recent movements (last 10 actions, live updating)
- Top 5 products by quantity
- Stock movements chart (last 7 days  IN vs OUT)
- Category breakdown (pie/donut chart)

All widgets auto-update in real-time via Socket.IO events. No page refresh needed.

---

### 7.6 Movement History & Audit Log

**Features:**
- Full paginated log of every stock movement ever made
- Filter by: product, user, movement type, date range, location
- Each record shows: product name, old qty, change, new qty, user, timestamp, note
- Export filtered results to PDF or Excel
- Movement history cannot be altered (immutable audit trail)

---

### 7.7 Reports & Export

**Available reports:**
1. **Current Stock Report**  snapshot of all products with quantities and values
2. **Low Stock Report**  all items below minimum threshold
3. **Movement Report**  all movements in a date range
4. **Category Summary**  stock value per category
5. **Product Valuation**  total inventory value breakdown

**Export formats:**
- PDF (using `pdfkit`  server-rendered, professional layout with logo)
- Excel/XLSX (using `exceljs`  full spreadsheet with formatting)

---

### 7.8 Alerts & Notifications

**In-app alerts (real-time):**
- Low stock toast notification when any product drops below its `minStock` threshold
- Out-of-stock alert when quantity reaches 0
- Notification bell icon in navbar with unread count

**Optional email alerts:**
- Low stock daily digest (if SMTP is configured in `.env`)
- Configurable: which user roles receive alerts

---

### 7.9 Settings & Configuration Panel

Accessible to Admin only. Covers:

- **Business Info:** name, address, currency, logo (used in reports and labels)
- **Locations:** manage warehouse/location names
- **Users:** add, edit, deactivate user accounts, change roles
- **Low Stock Defaults:** set default minimum threshold for new products
- **Backup:** export full DB as SQL dump, import from backup
- **Optional Modules:** toggle Sales Tracking, Label Printing (on/off)

