## 10. Real-Time Strategy

### Implementation Pattern

```
Client A (adds stock)     Server              Client B (viewing dashboard)
                                                     
       POST /inventory/add                           
                               
                            DB updated               
                            emit("stock:updated")    
                           
       { success: true }                              dashboard updates
                                (no refresh needed)
```

### Socket.IO Room Strategy

All connected clients join a single shared room (`inventory`). Events are broadcast to this room. This is appropriate because it is a single-business system  all users see the same data.

### Connection Handling

- Clients auto-reconnect on disconnect (Socket.IO default)
- A reconnect fetches fresh data via REST to catch any missed events
- Connection status shown in UI (green/yellow dot in navbar)

