## 14. Release Strategy

### Semantic Versioning (SemVer)

All releases follow `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`:

| Increment | When |
|---|---|
| `PATCH` (1.0.**1**) | Bug fixes, security patches |
| `MINOR` (1.**1**.0) | New backward-compatible features |
| `MAJOR` (**2**.0.0) | Breaking changes, major redesigns |

### Release Process

```bash
# 1. Merge develop  release branch
git checkout -b release/1.2.0 develop

# 2. Bump version in package.json
npm version minor  # or patch / major

# 3. Update CHANGELOG.md (or auto-generate)
npx conventional-changelog -p angular -i CHANGELOG.md -s

# 4. PR: release/1.2.0  main
# After merge:

# 5. Tag the release
git tag -a v1.2.0 -m "Release v1.2.0"
git push origin v1.2.0

# 6. GitHub Actions auto-creates the release
```

### Labels for Issues & PRs

```
type: bug           confirmed bugs
type: feature       new feature request
type: docs          documentation
type: security      security issue
priority: critical  blocks release
priority: high
priority: low
status: in-progress
status: needs-review
status: blocked
module: inventory
module: auth
module: products
module: sales
module: labels
```

