## 15. Testing Strategy

### Test Types & Tools

| Type | Tool | What's Tested |
|---|---|---|
| Unit | Vitest | Individual functions, utilities, helpers |
| Component | Vitest + React Testing Library | React components in isolation |
| API Integration | Supertest | Every API endpoint (happy path + error cases) |
| E2E | Playwright | Full user flows (login  add product  check stock) |

### Required Test Coverage

- All API routes: 100% covered (Supertest)
- Business logic services:  80% coverage
- Frontend components:  60% coverage
- E2E critical paths: login, add product, stock movement, export report

### Test Database

- Separate test PostgreSQL database (defined in `.env.test`)
- Seeded with fixture data before each test run
- Reset between test suites

### Key E2E Test Scenarios

1. Admin creates a category with custom fields
2. Admin adds a product in that category with all custom fields filled
3. Staff logs in, records stock-in for the product
4. Second browser window opens dashboard  quantity updates in real-time
5. Stock drops below threshold  low stock alert appears
6. Admin exports stock report as PDF
7. (Optional) Admin processes a sale  stock auto-decrements

